article.headline: Wyoming 92, Kean 58
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Djibril Thiam scored 18 points as Wyoming was too big and athletic for Division III Kean in a 92-58 season-opening victory on Saturday night. The Cowboys had four players in double figures, as Amath M'Baye and Afam Muojeke scored 14 points each and Desmar Jackson added 12. Johnathan Jones scored 24 points for Kean, which designated the game as an exhibition. Kean, which is located in Union, N.J., led 12-6 before the Cowboys went on a 21-2 run. Wyoming was up 44-26 at halftime and led by as many as 36 points in the second half. Muojeke, who made four 3-point shots, played for the first time since a knee injury at Brigham Young in January.
